Miscellaneous Highlights: The ICC Men's T20 World Cup Africa Sub-regional Qualifier B will start on October 19 and will be held between October 19 and 24.
The top two sides will join the other four sides from sub-regional qualifiers A and C for the final.
The winners and the runners-up will then seal a spot for the 2026 T20 World Cup.
Others: The tournament will be hosted by Kenya and will feature hosts Kenya, Rwanda, Seychelles, Gambia, Zimbabwe, and Mozambique.
Namibia and Uganda have already qualified for the regional final qualifier after they participated in the 2024 T20 World Cup.
Zimbabwe, a Full Member of ICC, are participating in the tournament after missing out on direct qualification for the 2026 T20 World Cup.
